Package tsp

Class Ant

  • java.lang.Object
    • tsp.Ant
  • public class Ant
extends java.lang.Object
    A Ant is used to transverse a TSPGraph in order to find a solution to the Traveling Salesman Problem, that is, the Hamiltonian Cycle wth less cost.

    Each Ant has a reference to the TSPGraph that will transverse, a nestNode which is the end and start of every Hamiltonian Cycle and a visited array which saves the current current path of the Ant. It also saves the constants alpha, beta and gamma that define how the ant chooses the next node and how much pheromones it leaves on her trail after finishing a Hamiltonian Cycle.

    In summary Ant provides methods for:

    • Move the ant to the next node.
    • Check if a node has alrady been visited.
    • Get the ant choice for next node.
    • Get the next node weight.
    • Get the current path of the ant.
    • Check if the current path is already a Hamiltonian Cycle
    • Get the current best clyce and weight.
    The class has a static variable that saves the best cycle found so far and its cost.

    See Also:
    TSPGraph
